  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Africa Ministers Council on Water (AMCOW) in 2010 initiated a collaboration with Global Water Partnership (GWP) on climate adaptation in the water sector. More than 70 % of Africa&apos;s water resources are transboundary, hence the need for regional collaboration. AMCOW has requested GWP to assist in developing river basin and ground water management plans with the aim of improving water management and thereby avoid conflicts over water resources. AMCOW operates as the water unit under the African Union.
The program is designed for 5 years and is supported by Austria and the UK in addition the support from Denmark (25 million DKK).</narrative>
  </description>
